Pillow Image Processing Script
This Python script uses the Pillow library to perform various image processing operations, including resizing, rotation, text addition, filter application, contrast adjustment, and more.

Prerequisites
Before running the script, make sure you have the following prerequisites installed:

Python 3.x
Pillow library (pip install Pillow)
Usage
Clone the repository or download the script (image_processing_script.py) to your local machine.

Ensure you have an input image (input.jpg) in the same directory as the script.

Modify the script parameters or input image path if needed.

Run the script using the following command:

bash
Copy code
python image_processing_script.py
The script will display the altered image and save it as output_complex_updated.jpg in the same directory.

Features
The script incorporates the following features:

Resizing the image to a larger size.
Rotating the image.
Adding semi-transparent text with a gradient color.
Applying multiple filters (Blur and Sharpen).
Adjusting image contrast.
Adding a rectangle shape to the image.
Enhancing color saturation.
Feel free to customize the script parameters and explore additional features based on your requirements.

